Tom Vogt <tom@ricardo.de> wrote:
> when I buy a ticket, I buy "access" to the game. nobody pays for tickets
> just to be on the field. so if the owner throws me out I believe that he
> should refund all or part of the ticket price, because he is not
> delivering what I payed for (a live sports performance).

The only catch is that the fine print on the ticket tells you that by
using the ticket you are entering into an agreement whereby you can be
ejected from the game without refund.  This gets into contract law,
but ignoring this fine point, we basically agree.

